  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 3. Seven factors are assessed; two factors (Numerical solver error and Use error) are marked not-assessed with rationale citing 'beyond scope of current engagement' without concrete justification. Decision: Accepted despite unassessed factors at elevated model risk.",
